    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect byte order handling in pusharrays32 for negative values\n\n### Summary\nThe `pusharrays32` function in `nfapi/open-nFAPI/common/src/nfapi.c` incorrectly handles negative int32_t values due to improper sign extension during byte order conversion. This causes incorrect serialization of MBSFN subframe configurations containing negative values.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/common/src/nfapi.c`: Modified `pushs32` function to properly handle sign extension\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/common/src/nfapi.c`: Updated `pusharrays32` to use corrected byte order logic\n\n### Reproduction Steps\n1. Call `pusharrays32` with an array containing negative int32_t values (e.g., -1, -1000, 0x80000000)\n2. Observe that the serialized bytes do not correctly represent the two's complement representation\n3. When deserializing with `pullarrays32`, the original negative values are not restored correctly\n4. This specifically affects MBSFN configuration handling where negative timing adjustments are used\n\nThe issue manifests as incorrect RF timing adjustments in RRC reconfigurations when negative values are present in the MBSFN subframe configuration parameters.\n"
}